<!-- views/firm/philosophy.ejs -->
<%- include('../partials/header', {
    pageTitle: pageTitle,
    pageDescription: pageDescription,
    path: path
}) %>

<!-- Hero -->
<section class="bg-[#0f2e22] pt-24 md:pt-32 pb-14 md:pb-20 px-6 md:px-16">
    <div class="max-w-screen-xl mx-auto">
        <span class="font-sans text-sm font-bold text-white/60 uppercase tracking-widest block mb-4">The Firm</span>
        <h1 class="font-serif text-3xl sm:text-4xl md:text-5xl lg:text-6xl text-white tracking-tight mb-6">Mission &amp; Philosophy.</h1>
        <p class="font-sans text-xl text-white/80 max-w-3xl leading-relaxed">A partnership forged between brothers at West Point&mdash;built on shared values, shared ambition, and a conviction that real estate is the most direct way to leave a lasting mark on the communities we call home.</p>
    </div>
</section>

<!-- ═══════════════ A PARTNERSHIP OF INTENT ═══════════════ -->
<section class="bg-white py-14 md:py-24 px-6 md:px-16 border-b border-[#0f2e22]/10">
    <div class="max-w-screen-xl mx-auto grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-12 gap-10 md:gap-16">
        <div class="md:col-span-4">
            <h2 class="font-serif text-3xl md:text-4xl text-[#0f2e22] leading-tight">A Partnership<br/>of Intent</h2>
        </div>
        <div class="md:col-span-8">
            <div class="prose max-w-none font-sans text-lg text-gray-700 leading-relaxed space-y-6">
                <p>Vanier Capital was not conceived in a boardroom. Its founders met as cadets at the <strong>United States Military Academy at West Point</strong>, where they forged the kind of bond that only shared discipline, shared hardship, and shared purpose can produce. They became not just friends but brothers&mdash;a distinction that matters.</p>
                <p>About a year after graduating, a call to reconnect and catch up turned into something more. The conversation drifted toward a shared dream: finding a plot of land, developing it, building a place where their families could gather for years to come. That simple, personal vision&mdash;a place of their own&mdash;laid the foundation for what would become Vanier Capital.</p>
                <p>The ambition grew naturally from there. If they could build that for themselves, they could provide it for others. The scope expanded from a single dream into a clear mandate: improve existing residential housing, develop new residential and commercial properties, and leave a lasting, positive mark on the communities they operate in. Not as distant investors, but as people with genuine stakes in the neighborhoods they serve.</p>
                <p>They say friends make bad business partners. Vanier Capital was founded on the belief that brothers make exceptional ones.</p>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>
</section>

<!-- ═══════════════ THE FIDUCIARY STANDARD ═══════════════ -->
<section class="bg-[#f9f8f6] py-14 md:py-24 px-6 md:px-16 border-b border-[#0f2e22]/10">
    <div class="max-w-screen-xl mx-auto grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-12 gap-10 md:gap-16">
        <div class="md:col-span-4">
            <span class="font-sans text-xs font-bold text-gray-400 uppercase tracking-[0.2em] block mb-3">I</span>
            <h2 class="font-serif text-3xl text-[#0f2e22] leading-tight">The Fiduciary<br/>Standard</h2>
        </div>
        <div class="md:col-span-8">
            <div class="prose max-w-none font-sans text-lg text-gray-700 leading-relaxed space-y-6">
                <p>We do not chase speculative trends. Every capital deployment decision is guided by advanced quantitative modeling, conservative leverage assumptions, and an unwavering commitment to principal preservation. Our underwriting discipline is not an aspiration&mdash;it is a structural requirement baked into every acquisition thesis before a single dollar is committed.</p>
                <p>This means we frequently decline opportunities that others pursue. We maintain strict debt coverage ratios, stress-test against adverse scenarios, and refuse to rely on appreciation alone to generate returns. The result is a portfolio engineered for resilience&mdash;one that performs through market cycles, not merely during favorable conditions.</p>
                <p>To our capital partners, we offer a simple commitment: your capital is treated with the same discipline and scrutiny we apply to our own. Full transparency, conservative assumptions, no conflicts of interest.</p>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>
</section>

<!-- ═══════════════ RESIDENT-FOCUSED OPERATIONS ═══════════════ -->
<section class="bg-white py-14 md:py-24 px-6 md:px-16 border-b border-[#0f2e22]/10">
    <div class="max-w-screen-xl mx-auto grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-12 gap-10 md:gap-16">
        <div class="md:col-span-4">
            <span class="font-sans text-xs font-bold text-gray-400 uppercase tracking-[0.2em] block mb-3">II</span>
            <h2 class="font-serif text-3xl text-[#0f2e22] leading-tight">Resident-Focused<br/>Operations</h2>
        </div>
        <div class="md:col-span-8">
            <div class="prose max-w-none font-sans text-lg text-gray-700 leading-relaxed space-y-6">
                <p>We do not simply acquire property; we steward assets. Our conviction is that the quality of the resident experience is not a soft metric&mdash;it is the most reliable leading indicator of long-term financial performance. Stable, satisfied residents produce stable, predictable cash flow. It is that direct.</p>
                <p>This philosophy manifests in every operational decision: responsive maintenance systems, transparent lease processes, thoughtful capital improvements that prioritize livability over cosmetic appeal, and a management infrastructure designed to reduce friction at every touchpoint.</p>
                <p>Whether we are improving existing residential properties or developing new residential and commercial assets from the ground up, the objective is the same: bridge the gap between institutional capital efficiency and the human necessity of high-quality spaces. We aim to leave a permanent, positive mark on the communities in which we operate&mdash;the same communities where we live and where our families gather&mdash;ensuring that every deployment of capital results in a tangible elevation of quality of life and a durable return for our partners.</p>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>
</section>

<!-- ═══════════════ BUILT TO LAST ═══════════════ -->
<section class="bg-[#0f2e22] text-white py-14 md:py-24 px-6 md:px-16">
    <div class="max-w-screen-xl mx-auto grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-12 gap-10 md:gap-16">
        <div class="md:col-span-4">
            <span class="font-sans text-xs font-bold text-white/40 uppercase tracking-[0.2em] block mb-3">III</span>
            <h2 class="font-serif text-3xl text-white leading-tight">Built<br/>to Last</h2>
        </div>
        <div class="md:col-span-8">
            <div class="prose max-w-none font-sans text-lg text-white/80 leading-relaxed space-y-6">
                <p>Vanier Capital began with a dream about a single plot of land and a place for family to gather. That dream has grown, but the core has not changed. We are not building a portfolio of transactions&mdash;we are building something we intend to stand behind for a long time. A permanent collection of residential and commercial assets, improved through hands-on operations, disciplined reinvestment, and the patience that comes with genuine ownership.</p>
                <p>We want to be known as a firm that does what it says: operates with transparency, treats partners&rsquo; capital with the same care as our own, and leaves the communities we work in better than we found them. That is the standard, and we hold ourselves to it&mdash;because these are our communities too.</p>
                <p>We measure success not in quarters, but over the long run. Every asset we acquire, every community we develop, and every relationship we build is evaluated against a simple question: <em>will this endure?</em></p>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>
</section>

<!-- ═══════════════ CTA ═══════════════ -->
<section class="bg-[#f9f8f6] border-t border-[#0f2e22]/10 py-14 md:py-20 px-6 md:px-16">
    <div class="max-w-screen-xl mx-auto text-center">
        <h3 class="font-serif text-2xl md:text-3xl text-[#0f2e22] mb-4">Partner With Us</h3>
        <p class="font-sans text-lg text-gray-600 max-w-2xl mx-auto mb-8">We welcome conversations with institutions, family offices, and accredited individuals who share our conviction in disciplined, long-duration real estate investing.</p>
        <div class="flex flex-col sm:flex-row items-center justify-center gap-4">
            <a href="/contact/investor-relations" class="inline-block bg-[#0f2e22] text-white font-sans text-sm font-bold uppercase tracking-widest px-8 py-4 border border-[#0f2e22] hover:bg-[#1a1a1a] transition-colors">Investor Relations</a>
            <a href="/firm/overview" class="inline-block bg-transparent text-[#0f2e22] font-sans text-sm font-bold uppercase tracking-widest px-8 py-4 border border-[#0f2e22] hover:bg-[#0f2e22] hover:text-white transition-colors">Firm Overview</a>
        </div>
    </div>
</section>

<%- include('../partials/footer') %>
